k to summarize the experiences of the previous Parliament's four-year work or even to try to allude to it. (10.10) I will not undertake to give an answer to the question that always arises: did the people of the country vote for something or against something. But this much, I think, I can safely say that he voted for the expected future, just as he also wants to see his future as certain and predictable, and as peaceful - and as soon as possible -, one that takes him forward in time and not backward, and that the from the past - from any kind of past - he is ready to incorporate as much into his future as will make it stronger socially and economically, and which is in line with his moral value judgment. Because his natural wisdom demands social justice, sane equality of opportunity - he doesn't expect miracles or fried pigeons. You can sense good intentions, true words, dialogue, a say in the fate of property, even more so public purity. And make sure that they recognize all of this - as well as their opponent - verbally, in writing, and on screen. My recent conversations with the leaders of the six parliamentary parties, the tough discussions and the outcome of the coalition negotiations have convinced me that both the parties of the future government coalition and the future opposition are aware of the country's problems, the - by no means easy - tasks ahead of us, and they judge them similarly. the order of importance of the tasks of the National Assembly, so they are ready for fruitful dialogue, constructive debate and cooperation. Finally, I ask for God's blessing on the work of the National Assembly. I wish from the bottom of my heart to all the members of the House that what you do as a representative of the national assembly will benefit our country even if measured by the standards of your own conscience. (Applause.) Dear Parliament! I announce that in accordance with Section 2 (1) of the Rules of the House, 383 elected representatives have submitted their credentials by the time of the inaugural meeting. Dear Parliament! Pursuant to § 4 of the House Rules, until the election of the officers, the constituent meeting is chaired by the group president, and the four youngest representatives perform the secretarial tasks as the group registrars. As far as I know, the oldest representative is Dr. László Varga, representative of the Christian Democratic People's Party. (Applause.) The four youngest representatives: László Botka (MSZP), Tamás Deutsch (Fidesz), Péter Nahimi (MDF) and József Rimóczi (MSZP). I would like to ask the honorable Parliament if they are aware of anything else, are these data accurate? (No one applies.) Dear Parliament! To fulfill the duties of the co-chairman, Dr. I am asking representative László Varga, and the clerkship duties will be performed alternately by representatives László Botka and Tamás Deutsch, Péter Nahimi and József Rimóczi. I made the credentials available to the class president and the class registrars for the purpose of mandate examination. With this, I will hand over the leadership of the meeting to the co-chairman of the Parliament, and the two consecutive co-registrars will be Péter Nahimi and József Rimóczi. (Applause. - The President of the Republic, leaving the rostrum, shakes hands with Dr. László Varga, who is standing at the steps of the platform, and then takes his place according to the order of the meeting. - The president of the quorum, the quorum clerks and the secretary general of the National Assembly take their place at the presidential rostrum.)
